1.0 SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW

1.1 Core Design Philosophy

AREPS implements a progressive autonomy hierarchy where each module operates as an independent agent within a federated industrial system. The architecture follows a biological metaphor - SSF as spinal column, modules as specialized organs, PCDM as autonomic nervous system.

1.2 System Specifications

```
Total System Mass: 42.3 metric tons (Earth-launched)
Operational Mass on Mars: 15.8 metric tons (local counterweights)
Throughput Capacity: 125 kg/hour of <500Î¼m powder (nominal)
Power Consumption: 48.2 kW peak, 32.7 kW average
Operational Temperature: -80Â°C to +30Â°C (survival to -120Â°C)
Design Lifetime: 10 Earth years (with robotic maintenance)
Autonomy Level: ISO 21448 SOTIF Level 4 (full situational awareness)
```

1.3 Modular Breakdown

```
[LANDER 1] Structural Spine & Frame (SSF) + Power Core
[LANDER 2] Excavation Module (EM) + Primary Crusher (PCM)
[LANDER 3] Secondary Pulverizer (SPM) + Sieving Module (SCM)
[LANDER 4] Robotic Maintenance Kit + Spare Cartridges
```

