2.4 Fault Recovery Protocol

Scenario A - Rock Wedge:

```
1. Torque spike >150% nominal triggers immediate stop
2. Reverse rotation at 50% torque for 360Â°
3. Deploy percussive hammer (3kJ impact) on obstruction
4. If persistent, execute "dig-around" pattern
5. Mark coordinates for later robotic extraction
```

Scenario B - Dust Ingress:

```
1. Acoustic sensors detect bearing noise change
2. Activate purge cycle: COâ‚‚ blast through seal interfaces
3. Increase lubrication injection rate by 300%
4. If temperature rises >10Â°C above baseline, reduce RPM by 50%
```

