15.0 RISK MITIGATION STRATEGY

15.1 Technical Risks

Abrasive Wear:

Â· Mitigation: Redundant wear surfaces, quick-change cartridges
Â· Monitoring: Real-time thickness measurement, acoustic emission

Dust Ingress:

Â· Mitigation: Multi-stage sealing, positive pressure, electrostatic repulsion
Â· Recovery: Robotic seal replacement, internal cleaning cycles

Power Variability:

Â· Mitigation: Hybrid nuclear/solar, energy storage, load shedding
Â· Adaptation: Variable throughput based on available power

Autonomy Edge Cases:

Â· Mitigation: Extensive simulation testing, safe modes, Earth override
Â· Learning: Continuous improvement from operational data

15.2 Operational Risks

Single Point Failures:

Â· Design: No single failure stops entire system
Â· Recovery: Graceful degradation, alternative material paths

Communication Delays:

Â· Autonomy: Full local decision-making capability
Â· Verification: Earth confirmation for major actions only

Environmental Extremes:

Â· Design: Conservative temperature margins, dust storm protection
Â· Monitoring: Predictive weather modeling, preemptive actions

